        "evidence": "<p>Urine output [cc/kg/hr] = Actual[cc/day] / (weight [kg]*24)</p>",
        "facts": "<p>The normal range for 24-hour urine volume is 800 to 2000 milliliters per day (with a normal fluid intake of about 2 liters per day).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Oliguria is urine output &lt; 500 mL in 24 h (0.5 mL/kg/h) in an adult.</li>\n<li>Oliguria is urine output &lt; 1 L in 24 h (1 mL/kg/h) in a child.</li>\n</ul>",
